The largest price increase in August 2008 occurred in the leather and shoe processing sector (2.8%), mainly bags and belts at 4.6% and shoe production at 2.5% monthly increase.
The high price level of plastics and chemical raw materials caused a significant monthly increase (1.6%) in the chemicals and products sector.
A decrease in prices occurred in the oil processing sector (1.4%), in the production of electrical tools and machinery (0.9%) and to a minimum in wood processing (0.1%)
The prices of paper production, publishing and printing activities have not changed.
In the other sectors of the manufacturing industry there was a price increase of between 0.2 and 0.9%.
