In the other sectors of the manufacturing industry the pace of price increases ranged from 0.6% to 9.1%.
In total in the processing industry in the past year prices rose by 10.2%.
Prices in the electricity, gas, steam and water supply sector were 18.7% higher than last year.
In domestic sales among the target groups of sectors, the largest monthly price increase occurred in August in the sectors producing investment goods (0.7%).
In the sectors that produce consumer items, prices rose by 0.3%, in the energy and post-consumer sectors, prices did not change compared to the previous month.
In August 2008, compared to the same month last year, the largest price increase was observed in the energy and later use sector (16.8%).
In the sectors that produce consumer goods the increase was 6.8%, for investment goods a decrease of 1.4% was measured.
Industrial export sales prices calculated in guilders increased in August by 1.1% compared to the previous month, compared to 12 months decreased by 3.9%.
