Today in Paris has started the European Summit for Equal Opportunities, organized this year from France having the presidency of the European Union.
Lívia Járóka, Fidesz deputy of the European People's Party in the message addressed to the plenary as the main rapporteur of the congress drew attention to school segregation because it is the most serious legal violation that affects Roma children and in addition the most serious obstacle to their affirmation.
